Text.SourceString: Oh, hello! I don’t think we’ve met.
I’m <NPCName>Aaliyah</>.
Planning to go to the Cherry Blossom Festival, <PlayerName>$player</>? You don’t want to miss it!
<NPCName>Frank</> will be manning the grill, and my brother is more or less the grill master of Coral Island, so…
Did you enjoy the Cherry Blossom Festival? I ate so much I could hardly walk home!

I don’t mind the cold weather and stuff, but nothing, and I mean, <Italic>nothing</> beats eating outdoors.//But it’s much better in Spring than in the middle of an ice-cold Winter afternoon, of course.
Enjoying Spring so far?
Are you going to <NPCName>Bree’s</> for the New Year’s feast? It’s going to be a good time!
My brothers and I used to build snow forts in weather like this. Our snowball wars were epic!
Now that I’m home, I don’t get to fly as much… I miss it! I’m itching to get back in the cockpit.
I wouldn’t let Mama hear me say that, though. She seems to think I’m home for good.//It’ll be easier for everyone if we let her keep thinking that until I have to leave again.
Or maybe it makes it worse…? I just don’t want unnecessary conflict, is all.//Not while I’m living under the same roof with her.
<NPCName>Chaem</> is fun to play volleyball with. She’s really good.//Learning a lot of tricks and stuff from her.
When I was in basic training, they made us camp out for three days in weather like this.//A test of endurance and your ability to stay cooped up in a small space with a bunch of people.
You know what I’m craving right now, <PlayerName>$player</>? A nice hot cup of coffee…//I’m gonna go and get some.
You know what I’m craving right now, <PlayerName>$player</>? A nice, hot cup of coffee…//I’m gonna go and get some.
You know what I’m craving right now, <PlayerName>$player</>? A nice, hot cup of coffee…//I’m gonna go and get some.
You know what I’m craving right now, <PlayerName>$player</>? A nice, hot cup of coffee…//I’m gonna go and get some.
You know, I’m glad to be back on Coral Island, but it’s not quite the same without my dad and my little brother here.
Mama’s been baking up a storm lately. I keep telling her, “Don’t tempt me – I have to stay in shape!”//But then she waves a chocolate chip muffin under my nose, and that’s it, I’m gone.
Do you have more layers at home you can wear?//<portrait=normal>Winter is next week, and it seems like it might be a cold one this year.
Now that it’s Fall, Mama can’t stop baking mooncakes at home.//<portrait=happy>It’s not that I want her to, anyway. Heh heh!
I’m A-OK to spend my whole Summer at the beach, playing volleyball.//But the thing is, I can’t seem to find any partners other than <NPCName>Chaem</>.
Yeah, <NPCName>Paul</> is there sometimes and stuff. Just not often enough, you know?
I can’t imagine going to the hot spring in this heat.//But I heard from my friend <NPCName>Chaem</> that the hunter dude goes there in Summer.
Playing volleyball with <NPCName>Chaem</> pushes me to be a better player… I like it.//It makes me better, <Italic>and</> I get to work out.
Besides, she told me she needed a partner to train with.//<portrait=normal>I mean, if I can be of help, why not, right?
Every several weeks or so, <NPCName>Eddy</> does his disappearing act where he doesn’t answer mail and makes Mama all worried.
I’m gonna have to snoop on social media and find out what he’s up to.//<portrait=angry>He’s got me all worried too!
Being outdoors on a warm Spring day like this is my favorite.//Get that vitamin D, move your body… When your mind is clear, your day will be too.
I’m glad to be where I am in life, but I can’t stop here, no. I wanna keep educating myself…reach for the stars, as it were.//<portrait=normal>I gotta set a good example for my little brothers.
The weekend’s here. I’m gonna get <NPCName>Noah</> to play volleyball with me tomorrow.//<portrait=annoyed>He’s probably gonna say no again. It’s hard to get that one to do any sports.
Going on a walk?//I’m here to train. Gotta keep fit to be an astronaut…and smart.//<portrait=concerned>Oof, a lot of things to keep up with! But I’ll be okay.//<portrait=angry>I will be A-OK… Yep!
*left eye twitches*
I’m ready to relocate my family to the city if I have to… You know, with the whole oil spill thing.//It hasn’t gotten that bad, I suppose.

I see your work around the community, <PlayerName>$Player</>. Respect! I’d tip my hat to you if I were wearing one!//<portrait=happy>I don’t shy away from hard work either… I see we have a lot in common.
You’re one reliable farmer, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//I like that trait in a person.
Gah! I got sand in my mouth!
The beach is nice this time of year.//<portrait=happy>Well, the beach is nice <Italic>any</> time of year, to be honest. Especially when the weather is perfect like this.
It brings back a lot of childhood memories.
That volleyball thing over there…it’s been here since I was little.//But the bright-red color is new.
The whole area, including the chair, used to be blue.
Going on a walk?//I’m gonna have to wash my hair tonight… The smell of the ocean is strong today.
I like getting coffee at <NPCName>Raj’s</> place.//They’re good at making coffee – my favorite!

They once told me about how every cup is special – creating one is a work of art, things like that.//<portrait=happy>It works, though! Because the coffee at their place just tastes better than it does at home. I don’t know how to describe it.
Don’t let the heat get you, <PlayerName>$Player</>!//Power through!
Whoa! The farmer is here!//<portrait=normal>You look like you’re ready for Summer. Good for you.
Thankfully I’ve fixed Fishensips’ ventilation just in time for Summer. It turned out there were clumped-up leaves stuck in there.//<portrait=annoyed>Gah!
Could’ve been worse, I guess… It could’ve been a dead rat or worse…
The grass changes color in Summer. Did you notice that?
Winter is nice here. I like the snow in the trees.//<portrait=annoyed>Only in trees! When there’s snow on the path – that’s different.
At the rate it’s been snowing, I’ll be out shoveling every day starting tomorrow.
Do you think you might enter the crop display contest at the Harvest Festival?//<portrait=surprised>You should! You might win something!
Saw <NpcName>Lily</> cleaning up her mom’s grave the other day.//It must’ve been the day when–
It’s never easy to lose a parent… It wasn’t easy when I was little, and it isn’t easy now.//I feel for her and her brother.
It sure doesn’t sound like a bad idea to fly over Coral Island right now. Just when the leaves are changing color.
Do you grow trees on your farm? I heard they don’t die.//Food for thought.
Mama likes to be busy… I told <NpcName>Noah</> that it’s best to just let her.//It’s good for her to have activities so she doesn’t just sit around the house.
Don’t always believe everything you hear around here.//One time I heard a rumor from my own little brother about a ghost playing the piano in the community center. Yada yada yada.
To have a ghost is one thing. Now they play the piano <Italic>too</>?//<portrait=angry>Where would they even learn to do such a thing?
One day I’ll go to visit the moon.//<portrait=happy>No, I’ll get <Italic>paid</> to visit the moon. Now, that’s cool!
I used to dream about going to the moon when I was little. Mama told us about the Moon Goddess and her rabbit.//<portrait=normal>I wanted to go there too. Ha ha! Thought it was the coolest thing.
Oh hey, by the way… I like chatting with you.//You’re smart. You know a lot of things, that’s for sure!

I like to eat the same things, especially for lunch.//It’s simple, you know? Eggplant lasagna or some hummus with <Italic>things</>. I just made a bunch of food and put it in the fridge.//<portrait=happy>It’s one less thing to think about in the morning.
Miss the snow yet?
Whatever you bring to the Cherry Blossom Festival, please don’t let it be brussels sprouts. Yuck!
Blech! Sorry! Don’t worry about it.//<portrait=normal>You can bring whatever you want.
Do you grow strawberries on your farm? If you don’t, you should!//They’re so good when they’re fresh. My absolute favorite fruit.
Tell me, <PlayerName>$player</>, do you think you’ll stick around on Coral Island? What’s your master plan?
Yeah, I hear you. My career took me away from Coral Island for a bit, but this place is always home.

Special.SourceString: I think I will! I like it here.

Text.SourceString: Hmm. I get it, I do. You have to go where you need to be, know what I’m saying?//But I hope you’ll stick around for a while. We’re just getting to know each other.

Special.SourceString: Not sure yet… This might just be a pit stop.

Text.SourceString: Bring on the snow! Winter’s here, so let’s get on with it. *laughs*
Spring is cool, but poor <NpcName>Char</>–//<portrait=happy>Ah! I’m just messing with you! Ha ha!
Gah! People here can get all over your business, right? Everyone keeps talking about poor <NpcName>Charles</> this, poor <NpcName>Charles</> that.//<portrait=concerned>Leave the man alone, people!
Hey, <PlayerName>$player</>. Did you stop in for a drink?
If you want to order, go to the counter. <NPCName>Frank</> will take care of you.
<PlayerName>$player</>, want to watch some TV with me?//<portrait=normal>I don’t even know what I’m watching. I wasn’t paying attention.
I’m trying to unwind, but my brain’s going a mile a minute tonight.//It’s hard to stop it when my brain starts doing its <Italic>thing</>.

The trickiest part about being in basic training is the confinement. You gotta be okay with being with people in a small space for a long time.//<portrait=happy>Good thing I grew up with a lot of siblings. Trained since childhood, if you ask me!
I’m looking forward to spending some time at the beach and soaking up the sun.
Eggplant lasagna is far superior to generic lasagna.//The texture is out of this world!
It’s a little chilly today. It’s kinda nice.
Have you heard of this show? I think it’s called Game of Cones? <NPCName>Noah’s</> always going on about it.
I tried watching it with him, but it just made me hungry.
Mama loves feeding the birds. She always has. When my brothers and I were kids, she taught us how to make bird feeders.//<portrait=happy>I still know how. I’ve just never done it.
My little brother and his friend, <NPCName>Alice</>, sure like talking about aliens. They have some…interesting theories.
The universe is big, so maybe we aren’t the only ones! But who knows?//<portrait=happy>If I see something when I’m in space, I’ll let you know. Ha ha!
I joined the military after university because I knew it was a path to becoming an astronaut.//<portrait=happy>Who doesn’t wanna be an astronaut?!
You can cook nice hot meals if you have a kitchen.//<portrait=happy>Now that it’s Winter, you might want to have hot dinners. Thaw out your frozen insides. Ha ha!
You wanna have a snowball fight?//<portrait=normal>C’mon! It’ll be fun.
I saw one of my brother’s cats on the roof the other day!//<portrait=normal>It was at Sam’s General Store. Do they go to your place too?

I help out my brothers at the Tavern sometimes, cleaning up, closing, business advice –
things like that.//It’s what big sisters are for, right?
So tell me, <PlayerName>$Player</>, as a <Italic>vegetable grower</>. Why do people care so much about the price of turnips?

Hmm… Maybe not here, on Coral Island.//I visited an island some Summers ago – the heat reminds me of that trip. Anyway, some of the villagers there get very excited over the price of turnips.//<portrait=happy>It was oddly wholesome to see.
It got pretty lonely at basic training. I missed my family.//<portrait=sad>Never leaving a place for months. That’s a long time.
We <Italic>did</> have a lot of things to do. The work never really stopped, so it wasn’t like we were sitting down, being bored.//<portrait=sad>But yeah. It gets to you sometimes.
Can’t wait to actually live on a spaceship up there and see Earth from above.//<portrait=happy>The view will be unbelievable!
Hopefully, with the rain this heavy, the sky will be clear by tomorrow night. It would be nice to stargaze, if you ask me.
Hopefully with the rain this heavy, the sky clears up tomorrow night. It would be nice to stargaze if you ask me.
It’s tricky to get some space in space…Heh heh!//<portrait=normal>Jokes aside, you gotta learn to coexist with others in a confined environment while under a <Italic>lot</> of stress.
Gotta say, it isn’t a walk in the park, but my siblings prepared me for it just fine.//<portrait=happy>I don’t think I’m doing so bad.
